<text type="translation" xml:lang="en">
    <body>
        <p>Your notification from <placeName ref="places.xml#yed01">Yedrovo,</placeName> dated the <date when-custom="1762-09-07">7th,</date> caused me some concern that
            the feverish attack, as you write, has again afflicted <persName ref="people.xml#pet04">His Highness.</persName> However,
            I think myself that the Yedrovo lodgings, and the people who disturbed him during my journey,
            are the reason. God grant that this passes. As for your care, I have not the slightest doubt.</p>
        <p>It seems to me that <persName ref="people.xml#pet04">His Highness</persName> will not reach
            <placeName ref="places.xml#mos01">Moscow</placeName> in time for my entry, and
            therefore you need not rush the journey but continue at your pace depending on the paroxysm’s condition.
            I shall wait until Thursday, but on Friday I will certainly enter the city, because it is absolutely impossible
            for me to delay further. I remain always well-disposed towards you.</p>
        <closer>
            <signed>
                <persName ref="people.xml#cat01">Catherine.</persName>
            </signed>
        </closer>
        <postscript>
            <p>
                <persName ref="people.xml#pan04">Your sister</persName> was with me this morning, and I found no change in her whatsoever.
                At <placeName ref="places.xml#med03">Mednoe,</placeName> the chambers of the old woman <persName ref="people.xml#shi01">Shishkova</persName> are far better than the palace,
                and in <placeName ref="places.xml#tve01">Tver</placeName> the Archbishop’s house is very good and made of stone; for this reason I advise
                you to stop there with the Grand Duke.
            </p>
            <closer>
                <placeName ref="places.xml#pet03">Petrovskoe village.</placeName>
                <lb/>
                <dateline>
                    <date when-custom="1762-09-10">10th of September, 1762</date>
                </dateline>
            </closer>
        </postscript>
    </body>
